Short version first: on Nobara + Rift S + SteamVR + VRChat, the “Monado + SteamVR” path is possible but still experimental and often breaks, and Rift S support is one of the least reliable parts of Monado right now. You can try it, but you should expect troubleshooting and possibly switching stacks (WiVRn is usually easier if you had a standalone headset; Rift S is trickier).

Here’s the actual working approach people use in 2026 for your exact goal.

1. Important reality check (Rift S + Monado)

Monado can:

Provide OpenXR runtime
Sometimes detect Rift S headset + tracking

But:

Rift S tracking/controller support is partial/experimental
SteamVR integration is not fully OpenVR-compatible out of the box
VRChat (SteamVR/OpenVR game) usually needs a bridge layer

So you typically need:

Monado (OpenXR runtime)

OpenComposite or xrizer (OpenVR → OpenXR translation)
SteamVR (only as launcher / compositor bridge)
2. Recommended stack on Nobara (what actually works most often)
Core components

Install:

monado (OpenXR runtime)
openxr-loader
steam
SteamVR
opencomposite OR xrizer (important)

On Fedora-based systems like Nobara:

sudo dnf install monado openxr-loader

SteamVR stays inside Steam.

3. Set Monado as your OpenXR runtime

Make sure Monado is active:

mkdir -p ~/.config/openxr/1

Check runtime file:

cat /usr/share/openxr/1/openxr_monado.json

Then link it:

ln -sf /usr/share/openxr/1/openxr_monado.json ~/.config/openxr/1/active_runtime.json

Verify:

echo $XR_RUNTIME_JSON

(Usually blank is fine if runtime file is correct)

4. Enable SteamVR to see Monado driver

Monado includes a SteamVR driver plugin.

Find SteamVR path:

~/.steam/steam/steamapps/common/SteamVR/

Register Monado driver:

./bin/vrpathreg.sh adddriver /usr/share/steamvr-monado

Check:

./bin/vrpathreg.sh

You should see “External Drivers”.

5. The critical missing piece: VRChat needs OpenVR translation

VRChat is OpenVR-based under SteamVR, not native OpenXR.

So you need ONE of these:

Option A (recommended): OpenComposite

Replaces SteamVR runtime layer.

Install OpenComposite and set:

export VR_OVERRIDE=/path/to/opencomposite

or use its “global override” mode.

Option B: xrizer (newer, more experimental)

Works better with Monado but still unstable for Rift S.

6. Start order (this matters a LOT)

Always start in this order:

Plug in Rift S (USB + DisplayPort)
Start Monado:
monado-service
Confirm tracking:
journalctl --user -u monado
Start Steam
Launch SteamVR
Launch VRChat
7. Common Rift S problems on Linux
Problem: headset detected but black screen
Usually compositor issue (Vulkan / DRM lease)
Try KDE Plasma X11 session (not Wayland)
Problem: SteamVR says “headset not found”
Monado driver not registered correctly
or OpenXR runtime not active
Problem: controllers missing
Rift S controller support in Monado is still incomplete in many builds
8. What most people end up doing on Nobara

Real-world outcome (important):

Monado + Rift S → partial success (headset tracking only)
SteamVR VRChat → unstable unless OpenComposite works perfectly
Controllers → often broken or drifting
